The Belagavi police got a moral boost with one of its senior official winning the prestigious Presidentâ€™s Medal for distinguished services.Rajiv S. Banahatti, currently serving as Assistant Commissioner of Police (Traffic) in Belagavi Police Commissionerate won the honour. He is among the 20 police officials from the State who were selected for the honour this year.Mr. Banahatti was felicitated by Minister for Small Scale Industries and district in-charge Satish L. Jarkiholi during Republic Day celebrations here on Tuesday.Mayor Kiran Sayanak, Feroz N. Sait, MLA, Sanjay B. Patil, MLA, Police Commissioner Soumendu Mukherjee and Superintendent of Police B.R. Ravikanthe Gowda and ZP CEO Bagadi Gautham were present.